#Install pip for Python2 in Kali

1. curl https://bootstrap.pypa.io/pip/2.7/get-pip.py -o get-pip.py
2. python2 get-pip.py

#Then, running the following commands should show:
pip -V  --> pip 20.3.4 from /usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/pip (python 2.7)
pip3 -V --> pip 21.0.1 from /usr/local/lib/python3.9/dist-packages/pip (python 3.9)

#To install packages, use the following commands
pip install "module" --> for Python2
pip3 install "module" --> for Python3

#Python2 links to Python2.7
#Python3 links to Python3.9